photos.name: Looking Out
photos.description: Looking out of a window of Delsbo Farmstead in Skansen, Stockholm. Outside in the snow some museum visitors are passing by.

photos.name: Stockholm - Skansen - Making Candles I
photos.description:
One of the farms in historic open-air museum Skansen in Stockholm is "Delsbogården". On the table some tools and materials for making candles (or rather the wicks for candles) are spread out.

More information on this historic farm:
The Delsbo Farmstead (Delsbogården) is made up of buildings from Hälsingland and illustrates what a prosperous farm looked like about 1850. Cultivating their fields and animal husbandry were the principal activities of the farmers but forestry and linen-production provided extra income. Profits from the sale of linen and an increased demand for timber brought prosperity to the district as is manifested by the large, sturdily built houses with their splendid porches and rich fittings. The farmers maintained regular trading contacts with the coastal towns and with the Norwegians who imported butter and ironwork as well as timber. (source: http://www.mynewsdesk.com/uk/pressreleases/living-history-at-skansen-the-delsbo-farmstead-544292).

photos.description:

photos.name: Stockholm - Skansen - Christmas Table II
photos.description:
Every year around Christmas time, the residential historians in historic museum Skansen in Stockholm create several historic Christmas tables. 
This one is in Delsbo Farmstead a farm from the 1850's which has been decorated as being from a well-to-do farmers family.
The number of candles on the table always had to correspond to the number of people at the table for good luck. The big piles of butter were more to show wealth than to eat. They were sold afterwards. The dishes shown here are "Lutefisk" Christmas Ham and Rice Porridge with cinnamon.

photos.name: Silence
photos.description: Shot outside Delsbo, a small village in the middle of Sweden. Taken on a moving pier so it took quite a few shot to end up with this. I like the contrasts.

photos.name: Pluto and Charon
photos.description: The model of Pluto and Charon resides in the little park immediately to the east of Staffansgården, near Kalvstigen in Delsbo, Hälsingland.

photos.name: Pluto and Charon
photos.description: A close up view of the model of Pluto and Charon in Delsbo. Pluto is here nearest of the two.

photos.name: Sweden Solar System, original version
photos.description: Sweden Solar System is the world's largest scale model of our Solar System, in the scale of one to 20 million. Our Sun is represented by the Globe in Stockholm, the world's largest spherical building. Originally there were models of planets out to Pluto and its largest moon Charon in Delsbo, but later the model was extended by including a few comets and several KBO's (Kuiper Belt Objects, i.e. asteroids outside Pluto), and finally the Terminal Shock (where our Solar System ends and interstellar space takes over) which is represented right outside Kiruna.
